This method allows setting individual bits of two 8-bit output registers (`0x02` and `0x03`) to control GPIO states on the XL9555 chip.

```cpp
void SetOutputState(uint8_t bit, uint8_t level)
{
    uint16_t data;
    int index = bit;

    if (bit < 8)
    {
        data = ReadReg(0x02);
    }
    else
    {
        data = ReadReg(0x03);
        index -= 8;
    }

    data = (data & ~(1 << index)) | (level << index);

    if (bit < 8)
    {
        WriteReg(0x02, data);
    }
    else
    {
        WriteReg(0x03, data);
    }
}
```

